<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1271">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/8924.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Private information not confirmed indicates Mexican Government gathering
                            information for the purpose of compelling foreign corporations as well
                            as native corporations to make forced loans to Mexican Government in the
                            form of purchase of bonds to relieve Government’s financial
                            condition.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>